Test various examples to see if they are valid or invalid.
Implements
  EOF1V4750_0001 (Valid) EOF code containing single type section - Data index: 0
  EOF1V4750_0002 (Valid) EOF code containing single type section and data section - Data index: 1
  EOF1V4750_0003 (Valid) EOF code containing multiple type/code sections - Data index: 2
  EOF1V4750_0004 (Valid) EOF code containing multiple type/code sections and data section - Data index: 3
  EOF1V4750_0005 (Valid) EOF code containing multiple type/code sections, no void I/O types - Data index: 4
  EOF1V4750_0006 (Valid) EOF code containing multiple type/code sections, no void I/O types, containing data section - Data index: 5
  EOF1V4750_0007 (Valid) EOF code containing RETF as terminating instruction - Data index: 6
  EOF1V4750_0008 (Valid) EOF code containing RETF as terminating instruction, containing data section - Data index: 7
  EOF1V4750_0009 (Valid) EOF code containing the maximum number of code sections - Data index: 8
  EOF1V4750_0010 (Valid) EOF code containing the maximum number of code sections and data section - Data index: 9
  EOF1I4750_0001 (Invalid) EOF code missing mandatory type section - Data index: 10
  EOF1I4750_0002 (Invalid) EOF code containing multiple type headers - Data index: 11
  EOF1I4750_0003 (Invalid) EOF code containing type section size (Size 1) - Data index: 12
  EOF1I4750_0004 (Invalid) EOF code containing type section size (Size 8 - 1 Code section) - Data index: 13
  EOF1I4750_0005 (Invalid) EOF code containing type section size (Size 8 - 3 Code sections) - Data index: 14
  EOF1I4750_0006 (Invalid) EOF code containing invalid section type (1,0) (First section having a type different than (0,0)) - Data index: 15
  EOF1I4750_0007 (Invalid) EOF code containing invalid section type (0,1) (First section having a type different than (0,0)) - Data index: 16
  EOF1I4750_0008 (Invalid) EOF code containing invalid section type (2,3) (First section having a type different than (0,0)) - Data index: 17
  EOF1V4750_0011 (Invalid) EOF code containing too many code sections - Data index: 18
  EOF1I4750_0009 (Invalid) EOF code containing CALLF to a non existing code section - Data index: 19
  EOF1I4750_0010 (Invalid) EOF code containing truncated CALLF - Data index: 20
  EOF1I4750_0011 (Invalid) EOF code containing deprecated instruction (JUMP) - Data index: 21
  EOF1I4750_0012 (Invalid) EOF code containing deprecated instruction (JUMPI) - Data index: 22
  EOF1I4750_0013 (Invalid) EOF code containing deprecated instruction (PC) - Data index: 23
  EOF1I4750_0014 (Invalid) EOF code containing call to functions without required stack specified in type section - Data index: 24
  EOF1I4750_0015 (Invalid) EOF code containing call to functions without required stack NOT specified in type section - Data index: 25
  EOF1I4750_0016 (Invalid) EOF code containing function trying to return more items than specified in type section - Data index: 26
  EOF1I4750_0017 (Invalid) EOF code containing function exceeding max stack items - Data index: 27
  EOF1I4750_0018 (Invalid) EOF code containing function which max stack height causes to exceed max stack items (stack overflow) - Data index: 28
